	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />How exactly does the bankswitching for Bill &amp; Ted's Excellent Video Game adventure work?  I noticed that the interrupt handler(?) was performing INC FFFF.  Does that write FF (value in rom at FFFF) then write 00 (FF+1)?  Any other surprise writes to ROM areas?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

